Acceptance Criteria:
1.	Lead can be reverted back to original Loan officer using batchId
2.	Lead re-transfer based on batchId can be tracked in LeadTransferRequestsCollection in mongo db
3.	When Lead is re-transfer or reverted, Status should change to PENDING in LeadTransferRequestsCollection
4.	Re-transfer process will complete when /process-lead-transfer endpoint runs
5.	Once process is completed, Lead should be re-transfer to original Loan officer and assignedToUser object on lead should have that Loan officer information
6.	When re-transfer process is completed, Status on batchId records should be changed to Success
Pre Conditions:

Suggested Steps to perform:
1.	Leads first needs to be transferred from Loan Officer A to Loan Officer B which can be done via below curl and this will return BatchId, note it down
curl --location 'https://leadapi.test.crosscountrymortgage.com/lead/transfer-leads' \
--header 'x-api-key: aJetMsoLJJPOA3qGblq4l006ccCr2g' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '
  {
    "fromEmployeeId": "c0f4a094-3649-4991-9970-f1cee128f86e",
    "toEmployeeId": "858d9c14-440b-4a4a-9d0c-fa2d67337c5a",
    "updatedBy": "21July2025"
}

2.	Run process endpoint to perform lead transfer for the batchId generated in Step 1
curl --location --request POST 'https://leadapi.test.crosscountrymortgage.com/lead/process-lead-transfer' \
--header 'x-api-key: aJetMsoLJJPOA3qGblq4l006ccCr2g' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json'

3.	Now, using the BatchId generated in step 1, run below endpoint to start re-transfer of lead back to Loan officer A from Loan Officer B
4.	Run process endpoint to perform lead transfer for the batchId generated in Step 3
curl --location --request POST 'https://leadapi.test.crosscountrymortgage.com/lead/process-lead-transfer' \
--header 'x-api-key: aJetMsoLJJPOA3qGblq4l006ccCr2g' \
5.	Verify LeadTransferRequests collection for the status
6.	Verify Leads in Leads collection has assigned to user with intended loan officer

Other Instructions:
1.	All steps should include numbering
2.	Write comprehensive testcases based on ACs and steps provided. 
3.	Cover all the scenarios you can think of
